            <h3 class="media-heading"><strong>

				Safety Relief Valve Vent Silencers<!--Safety Relief Valve Vent Silencers--></strong></h3>

            	The unexpected opening of an un-silenced safety relief valve can cause shock to nearby workers and annoyance to local communities, with sound pressure levels of 150dB(A) not uncommon. &nbsp;Our safety relief valve silencers are built to withstand the instant pressure release of the lifting valve, and provide the right pressure drop, to ensure that flow is not restricted.<!--The unexpected opening of an un-silenced safety relief valve can cause shock to nearby workers and annoyance to local communities, with sound pressure levels of 150dB(A) not uncommon. &nbsp;Our safety relief valve silencers are built to withstand the instant pressure release of the lifting valve, and provide the right pressure drop, to ensure that flow is not restricted.--><br />

